topic.title: TCP/IP Setting Block

body.p: The TCP/IP layer supports IPv4 addressing and provides support for baseline operations including frame management, retransmission, error checking. The TCP/IP stack can also support applications such as PING, DHCP and TELNET.

note.p: The default value of KEEPALIVE means:

The keepalive routines wait for two hours (KEEPALIVE TIME: 7200 secs) before sending the first keepalive probe, and then resend it every 75 seconds(KEEPALIVE INTV). If no ACK response is received for 5(KEEPALIVE PROBE CNT) consecutive times, the connection is marked as broken.
The configuration of TCPIP keep alive should satisfy following conditions:

li.p: KEEPALIVE TIME >= KEEPALIVE INTV * KEEPALIVE PROBE CNT
KEEPALIVE TIME is the integer multiple of KEEPALIVE INTV
